- Kernel: `/nix/store/pmr8rwjm5hyi92k5yaqxq687my7crsr6-riski5-linux-rv32-nommu-6.18.22`
  built from commit `e47e5f5` (overlay config has STACKPROTECTOR
  + STRONG + PER_TASK enabled).
- Verilator sim lib: `/nix/store/xqmmvp297hgi4524a4h3c7s961b2jysa-riski5-sim-0.1.0`
  (default `firmware="linuxBootSim"` variant).
- Driver: `cabal run riski5-linux-hwsim --flag=hwsim` against the
  above sim lib + the kernel + `/nix/store/i9649xc1am1dm5aa4bfy47wl54anwc4f-riski5-dtb-0.1.0/riski5.dtb`,
  cycle budget 1_000_000_000.
- Run wall clock: ~22 minutes for 1 B simulated cycles.
- Captured UART: 3068 bytes, last printk
  `Mountpoint-cache hash table entries: 1024`.
- PC histogram + per-100-M-cycle sample log saved at
  `/tmp/sp-hwsim-1g.log` (768 KB).
